summary: Did I hear right? You're doing matchups for Valentine's? If you could do one for me I would love you. I'm a straight female with...
question: Did I hear right? You're doing matchups for Valentine's? If you could do one for me I would love you. I'm a straight female with dark hair and blue eyes. Most people find me intimidating mostly because I don't speak much but that's just cause I have a darker sense of humor and interests including horror movies and serial killer documentarys. I'm a total sweetheart when I open up, quite the mom friend actually. Definitely an introvert though, happy to stay home with a book rather than go out.
answer:
Yepp~ you definitely heard right XDD thanks for being my first ever matchup!!^^

~~~

I match you up with….Toshinori Yagi!

He wouldn’t be intimidated by your initial impression at all and would have no trouble approaching you first, patiently improving your relationship to the point where you could feel comfortable enough to open up to him. He wouldn’t mind your more reserved nature the fact that you don’t really speak much at all, but would encourage you to be yourself around him without holding back, and would sincerely accept and love every part of you.

He’d wholeheartedly embrace your interests, and although your sense of humor is quite different from what he’s used to, he finds your darker jokes intriguing. He’d also agree to watch your genres of entertainment together without a second thought, though he’d definitely be hiding in the warmth of your embrace during the activity. You would also do him good, as you would be the person to stop him from overexerting his abilities and taking care of him in times of need, being his pillar of support in rough times. He’d also rather much enjoy quality time with you in the comfort of your home than go out, the both of you usually spending your free time curled up on the sofa, with you introducing your favourite novels for him to read.

I hope you like your result!

summary: Random and Weird BNHA Dream #1 (There May Never Be a #2)
title: Random and Weird BNHA Dream #1 (There May Never Be a #2)
body: I had a dream where Hagakure was Ojiro’s girlfriend and she was kidnapped by some low level villain who only got into UA because everyone (even the principal) thought he was the school janitor. So Ojiro makes a group with Shoji, Koda, Sato, and Aoyama. Mineta tries to join but is flung out of a window by the wind and he was never seen again. So Team Limited Screentime™ leave the campus and wander around the city for like 10 minutes and they only find the place Hagakure is being kept in because it was in a trash can that Aoyama fell in while he was staring at the camera instead of watching where he was going. The Trash Can led to the most barren evil lair ever with a single chair that Hagakure was strapped to. The evil janitor walks out of the shadows as is revealed to be Moonfish who somehow escaped custody and without the weird suit he looks hot. Moonfish then leaves the room for some reason and is never seen again so Limited Screentime Squad™ untie Hagakure only to find out she’s not there! So they leave the lair, wander around the city some more, then Aoyama fell into a trash can AGAIN somehow finding another lair, except this time it was the League of Villains (Mustard, Hot Moonfish, and Muscular included) t-posing around a Pentagram chanting some weird language no one can understand,but Hagakure was also there t-posing. She reveals that she was the traitor all along because she saw that the League of Villains t-pose and that’s what she wants to do forever. She breaks up with Ojiro who then runs out the room crying, then he comes back with a paper that says “Overly Winded Speech on why you shouldn’t be evil”. Then he just throws it some place and everyone t-poses and Hagakure finds this appealing so she leaves the League of Villains but oh no! It’s Toga! Everyone beats Toga up and leave the scene and Ojiro is crying, Shoji is just spinning around in the background, Koda is talking about taxes to a street rat, Aoyama is just staring at the camera, and Sato is just there looking like he blue screened of died. Then my alarm woke me up and we never found out if Hagakure was saved and if Ojiro will ever be happy again :(
